input_str: RCN Launching 330 Mbps Service in NYC Not to be outdone by Time Warner Cable's recent "Maxx" upgrades, New York-area overbuilder RCN today announced they're going to soon start offering a 330 Mbps tier of their own. According to the company announcement, the 330 Mbps down, 20 Mbps up tier will be made available to the company's entire New York City footprint starting in December.
